# üîµ Fragment with key (Important for Lists)

If using fragment inside `.map()`:

```jsx
items.map((item) => (
  <React.Fragment key={item.id}>
    <h2>{item.title}</h2>
    <p>{item.desc}</p>
  </React.Fragment>
));
```

‚öÝ Shortcut `<> </>` cannot accept key
So use `React.Fragment` when key is needed.

---

# üßÝ Behind the Scenes

Fragment is not rendered in real DOM.
It only helps React group elements internally.

So:

‚úî No extra node
‚úî Cleaner DOM
‚úî Better performance

---

# üéØ Interview Answer (Short)

React Fragments allow grouping multiple JSX elements without adding extra DOM nodes.
They help avoid unnecessary wrapper divs and keep the DOM clean.

